The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 16 October is 4,287 (496.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 12 October, there were 367 new confirmed cases (42.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 05 October, there were 298 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 23% ( 69 extra cases).
